window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>A high-society murder. A spirited lady detective. Can she outclass the killer before an innocent person takes the fall?&nbsp;</p> <p>London, 1923. Olive Belgrave needs a job. Despite her aristocratic upbringing, she’s penniless. Determined to support herself, she jumps at an unconventional job - looking into the background of her cousin’s fiancé, Alfred.&nbsp;</p> <p>Alfred burst into the upper crust world of London’s high society, but his answers to questions about his past are decidedly vague. Before Olive can gather more than the basics, a murder occurs at a posh party. Suddenly, every Bright Young Person in attendance is a suspect, and Olive must race to find the culprit because a sly murderer is determined to make sure Olive’s first case is her last.&nbsp;</p> <p><i>Murder at Archly Manor</i> is the first in the High Society Lady Detective series of charming historical cozy mysteries. If you like witty banter, glamorous settings, and delightful plot twists, you’ll love <i>USA Today</i> best-selling author Sara Rosett’s series for Anglophiles and mystery lovers alike.</p> <p>Travel back to the golden age of detective fiction with <i>Murder at Archly Manor</i>.<i>&nbsp;</i></p>";